# GPIB MCP — Windsurf install (#91)

Windsurf (Cascade) runs local **stdio** MCP servers, so this uses the same `GpibMcp.exe` directly.
Windsurf has no install deeplink, so add it via the config file (or the Cascade MCP UI).

## 1. Get the server
Download `__ZIP__` from the GitHub Release and unzip it to:

```
__INSTALLDIR__
```

(so the server is at `__EXE__`). NI-VISA / NI-488.2 must be installed on the machine.

## 2. Config
Add to `%USERPROFILE%\.codeium\windsurf\mcp_config.json` (merge into any existing `mcpServers`):

```json
__CONFIG__
```

Then in Windsurf: **Cascade → MCP / Manage plugins → Refresh**.

## 3. Use it
Confirm `gpib` appears in Cascade's MCP tool list, then ask it to talk to your instruments.
